description.p:
In another embodiment, the liquid dishwashing detergent consists essentially of: water;
5 to 30% by weight of an anionic surfactant;
5 to 30% by weight of a co-anionic surfactant;
0.5 to 10% by weight of polyethylene glycol;
0 to 15% by weight of a foam stabilizing surfactant; and,
0 to 15% by weight of optional ingredients; wherein the polyethylene glycol has a molecular weight ranging from about 400 to 1000, with the proviso that the liquid dishwashing detergent be essentially free of alkyl polyglucosides. The optional ingredients are selected from the group consisting of hydrotropes, perfumes, colorants, pH adjusting agents, opacifiers, biocidal agents, preservatives, inorganic salts, viscosity modifiers, and mixtures thereof.

claim.claim-text:
A liquid dishwashing detergent consisting essentially of:
water;
5 to 30% by weight of an anionic surfactant;5 to 30% by weight of a co-anionic surfactant;0.5 to 10% by weight of polyethylene glycol;0 to 15% by weight of a foam stabilizing surfactant; and,0 to 15% by weight of optional ingredients;
wherein the polyethylene glycol has a molecular weight ranging from 400 to 1000.

A method for the hand washing of a kitchen surface, comprising contacting
the kitchen surface with a detergent consisting essentially of:
water;
5 to 30% by weight of an anionic surfactant;5 to 30% by weight of a co-anionic surfactant;0.5 to 10% by weight of polyethylene glycol;0 to 15% by weight of a foam stabilizing surfactant; and,0 to 15% by weight of optional ingredients;
wherein the polyethylene glycol has a molecular weight ranging from 400 to 1000.
